Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Granny Smith Apple{1}. Toast @sourdough bread{4%slice}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, @olive oil{1%TBSP}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} until fluffy.

> For 4 servings, use all the garlic powder, juice from two lemon wedges, and 2 TBSP olive oil instead.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%ounce}, half the @walnuts{1%ounce}, and half the apple with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and as much lemon juice as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad and toasted sourdough between plates. Spread sourdough with as much ricotta mixture as you like. Top with remaining apple. Drizzle with @hot honey{1/2%ounce} and sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Serve.